<frame name="FR_Being_in_favor_of" ID="10007" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Cognitive_positions">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;A &lt;fen&gt;Cognizer&lt;/fen&gt; has a relatively fixed positive or negative point of view towards a &lt;fen&gt;Content&lt;/fen&gt;. A &lt;fen&gt;Side&lt;/fen&gt; in a debate concerning the &lt;fen&gt;Content&lt;/fen&gt; may stand in for the &lt;fen&gt;Content&lt;/fen&gt;. Unlike FR_Taking_sides, this frame only includes FEEs that can never include the meaning of this point of view being communicated to an interlocutor.

&lt;ex&gt;In interviews , it seems like &lt;fex name="cog"&gt;everyone&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;m&gt;is&lt;/m&gt; &lt;fex completely &lt;t&gt;against&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="cont"&gt;this expenditure&lt;/fex&gt; .&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
Distinctions with other frames:
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;

    ≠ &lt;frframe&gt;FR_Taking_sides&lt;/frframe&gt;: FR_Being_in_favor_of only includes FEEs that can never include the meaning of this point of view being communicated to an interlocutor whereas all of FR_Taking_sides' FEEs include this possible meaning.
&lt;ex&gt; &lt;/ex&gt;
    ≠ &lt;frframe&gt;FR_Awareness-opinion-certainty&lt;/frframe&gt;: the difference lies in the Cognizer believing in some content's truth (FR_Awareness-opinion-certainty) versus believing his (dis)agreement with some content (FR_Being_in_favor_of).
    &lt;ex&gt; &lt;/ex&gt;
    ≠ &lt;frframe&gt;Be_in_agreement_on_assessment&lt;/frframe&gt;: in Be_in_agreement_on_assessment, two agreeing parties are necessarily locally expressed, and can be expressed as a single plural NP, whereas the FR_Taking_sides and FR_Being_in_favor_of frames are used for occurrences in which either only one party is expressed.
    &lt;ex&gt; &lt;/ex&gt;
    ≠ &lt;frframe&gt;Judgment&lt;/frframe&gt;: the Judgment frame contains a Reason FE, and evokes an evaluation whereas there is no subcategorized Reason in FR_Being_in_favor_of, and the LUs mark binary side (in favor or against) with respect to the Content (Evaluee in the Judment frame).


    &lt;ex&gt; &lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;asf&gt;Relation to fndata-1.5&lt;/asf&gt; : New in ASFALDA. Close to FR_Taking_sides, but without the idea of potential communication of the (dis)approval.
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
